node.text:
Captain Chelsey Sullenberger and First Officer Jeffery Skiles saved all 155 people onboard US Airways Flight 1549 after the successfully crash landing on the Hudson River in what would become to be known as the miracle on the Hudson. 

Video: @maxlangleyimages 
Media: Con Edison, AFP News, Live ATC Clips, Inc., AliasAnimo, Port Authority New York & New Jersey, ABC News, Wikimedia
Thumbnail: Carolinas Aviation Museum

node.text:
United Airlines (UA) has reached an agreement with the Air Line Pilots Association (ALPA) to prevent the furlough of close to 3,000 pilots. The deal has been agreed in principle and is still to be approved by the leadership of the ALPA UA chapter.

Link to article: https://airwaysmag.com/airlines/ua-pilots-union-agree-to-deal-avoid-furloughs/

Video: Max Langley (@maxlangleyimages)
Media: United Airlines
Thumbnail: Liam Funnell (@downwindaviation_)

📚 Time for another episode of our fact Friday series. Ever wondered how Virgin Atlantic name their aircraft?

Virgin claim that the names take inspiration from music, film, literature, food and other British links. 

Even previous names of retired aircraft are reused if they are to good to go!

Pretty cool right?

📸: Ervin Eslami (@uk.jets)

📸 Our time is nearly over with our weekly featured photographer, Jack O’Brien (@deltacs100)!

But, we have time for one more cool photo! ✈

"Nothing demonstrates the F-35C’s capabilities of landing and taking off on an aircraft carrier better than a simulated carrier approach touch and go. Being able to catch this tactical jet cleaning the gear and flaps up is something I won’t soon forget!"
